CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 12, 1946, pg. 25 reads: "Reception Honors Popular Pair - Mr. and Mrs. Arthur C. Cocril were honored recently at an elaborate wedding reception held at the home of the bride's mother, Mrs. Mary J. Davis, 532 Francis Street. Many out-of-town guests were present at the affair, and the newlyweds received many beautiful and useful gifts.  Mr. Cocril is a native of Cincinnati, Ohio. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of three men and three women, including Mr. and Mrs. Arthur C. Cocril, behind four tiered wedding cake, posed at table in home of bride's mother Mary J. Davis, 532 Francis Street
